<br>
Simply put, I was gaming too much. I've been down the &quot;take a week off and change priorities&quot; road. I consider myself disciplined, just not when it comes to computer games. I had bought DAOC and played it a lot (for me) for three days when I got a justified ragging from my wife. Faced with a neat new game, and established characters on EQ that I didn't want to let go of, I knew either my marriage and RL family, or my gaming and on-line family were going to have to go. Sadly, RL faminly means more. Does it help you wonderful people to know it was close? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  (actually, it wasn't really, but I feel bad about dropping you all like a hot potatoe, even though I know I did the right thing.)<br>
<br>
I hope to someday access my character's through a friend or my brother's computer, and give what little I have in the way of items back to Random Acts, or to anyone on M-T. So, if you see me saying something in guild chat about giving stuff away, it is the absolute end.<br>
<br>
It's strange, but I haven't even turned the CP on. I wanted to sell the computer, knowing I would get back to it eventually, but my wife wants to keep it for her digital photo processing. Sheesh! Can you believe she is so selfish! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I'll probably peek in every once in a great while. I have to avoid this site, like most gaming sites, so that I don't start desiring to play again. However, the occasional visit to support you all for your wonderful actions is not something to avoid. <br>
<br>
As a true outsider, kudos to Random Acts, the most unselfish and friendly on-line group I've every known in any fashion. Keep on keeping on! Oh, and since I never got the chance to ask that one really important question......<br>
<br>
<br>
Can I get a rez?<br>
